      <h1>Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) Lab</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Introduction &amp; Overview</p>

      <h2>Objective</h2>

      <p>In this module, use Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) to send data between your Intel® Edison and your Intel ®IoT Gateway.</p>

      <p>By the end of this module, you should be able to:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Enable the Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) services on Linux.</li>
        <li>Turn the Intel® IoT Gateway into a BLE central module using the <strong>noble</strong> NodeJS library.</li>
        <li>Turn the Intel® Edison into a BLE perphiphal using the <strong>bleno</strong> NodeJS library.</li>
        <li>Send and receive a single sensor data value over BLE.</li> 
      </ul>

      <div id="start">
        <h2>Set up Bluetooth</h2>
        <div class="tldr">
          Run shell commands on <strong>both</strong> your Intel® Edison and Intel® IoT Gateway devices to enable the correct Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) services.
        </div>
        <p><a href="setup/index.html" class="link-button centered">Go to Set Up »</a></p>
      </div>

      <div id="done-setup">
